title: Subchapter A - Forms Authorized by Section 205.7
content:
Subchapter A - Forms Authorized by Section 205.7

State Regulations

General forms (Form GF-1 to GF-46)

Miscellaneous Forms (Form Misc. 1 to Misc. 2)

Juvenile Delinquency Forms (Family Court Act Article 3) (Form 3-1 to 3-49)

Child Support Forms (Family Court Act Articles 4, 5-B) (Form 4-1 to UCS-111)

Uniform Interstate Family Support Act Forms (Form UIFSA-1 to UIFSA-13)

Paternity Forms (Family Court Act Article 5) (Form 5-1 to 5-18)

Foster Care Forms (Social Services Law Section 358-A) (Form 358-a-1 to 358-a-7)

Foster Care Forms (Social Services Law Section 383-C) (Form 383-c-1 to 383-c-5)

Foster Care Forms (Social Services Law Sections 384, 384-C) (Form 384-1 to 384-c-1)

Guardianship Forms (Family Court Act Article 6; S.C.P.A.; Social Services Law Section 384-B) (Form 6-1 to TPR-16)

Person in Need of Supervision (Family Court Act Article 7) (Form 7-1 to 7-21)

Family Offense Forms (Family Court Act Article 8) (Form 8-2 to 8-7)

Child Protective Forms (Family Court Act Article 10) (Form 10-1 to 10-29b)

Destitute Child Forms (ยง 10-C-1 to 10-C-4)

Permanency Hearing Forms (Family Court Act, Article 10) (Form PH1 to PH8)

Uniform Child Custody Jurisdiction and Enforcement Act (UCCJEA) Forms (Form UCCJEA-1 to UCCJEA-19)

Surrender Forms (Form SURR-1 to SURR-8)

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
